Forever loved husband and Beagle Dad

This is one of the last videos I took of you, my love, doing two things you absolutely loved: playing with Pasta and Shadow and teaching gymnastics. I keep waiting for you to walk in the door or text me. Pasta and Shadow sleep on your favorite hoodie every night, and I know they miss you terribly. I will forever miss and love you with all of my being. I wish there was some way for you to let me know that you’re ok and I play the last voicemail you left me every night just to hear you say, “I love you so much babe.”Sleep strong my love. #rip #acrobaddict #joeputignano

I hope that this will be the last depressing thing I’ll post here, but I hope to all of you that read this, you understand the intense level of grief I’m experiencing with the passing of my Joey (@sobernursejoe). We had a visitation with him yesterday to see his physical form one last time before he was cremated. To my surprise, they completed that process and I was able to bring him home this morning. I am relieved to have him home but to have my husband, someone that I was attached at the hip to for 10-years, I am still hurting so very much. Now, through so many tears, I’ve finally got to tackle the awful and costly, administrative side of things that I must complete. 

I ask of all of you to make sure you hug, kiss, call, text, write little notes for those you love often, if not daily, because in an instant, you or they can be gone. That’s the one thing I take solace in, is Joe and I did this all the time, so we know how truly and deeply we love each other.

Sleep strong, my love.

It’s embarrassing to ask, and I would never under normal circumstances, but any monetary assistance anyone can provide will be so helpful, until I get back on my feet and especially now with the loss of Joe’s income.

https://gofund.me/05da63d6

To everyone that has donated, words cannot express my heartfelt gratitude. I’ll be reaching out to all of you in the coming weeks as I try to get a handle on life again.❤️

#rip #acrobaddict #joeputignano

I can’t believe it’s already been three weeks since my Joe passed away. I take refuge in going through and reading his journals. Although I smile through tears, reading his writings, I’m so grateful to have what was on his mind, his writings of the true love and bond we share, his struggles with his disease of addiction, and how hard he fought to stay sober.

I am so appreciative of how many of you have reached out. I’m still working my way through all the DMs and I will reply. It’s so awesome to know how many lives he touched in such amazing, positive and uplifting ways. Ways that only Joe could. I will carry this with me forever and continue the work he started. I’m also thinking about taking his journal writings and combining my own for a second installment of his #acrobaddict novel, picking up where the first one left off, where he and I meet and go from there. We always dreamed of writing books together.

Right now, in addition to his final expenses, I’ve now got to get our little Shadow into the vet to have a baby tooth extracted, that is now causing her problems. God, I wish he was here to help me deal with this. I’m dreading the cost this procedure, but no expense is so great for our angels. I’m so grateful and speechless as to how to thank all of you for the GoFundMe. So many of you have helped me out in this time where I’m struggling to figure all this out. I hate to post this again, but Joe’s coworkers at the Buffalo VA Hospital (@leah_meinhart) set up this GoFundMe for us to make ends meet while I’m still in such a deep state of fear, grief, all the expenses that I’ve got to handle. Here’s the link, and know again that your help is truly alleviating so many of the stressors that I’m facing.

https://gofund.me/05da63d6

“Sleep strong, babe. I’ll be home soon.”

#joeputignano #rip

I wish there was a way to make this a happy post, but this last month has been so dark and sad for me. I found some old frames and added more to my Joe’s memorial. I’m still without words for the generosity of @guiguou and @mariemoongoddess for providing me with Joe’s #cirquedusoleil Crystal Man costume from #totemcirquedusoleil. I’m beside myself with emotion to have this because he always talked about wanting one of his costumes from that show. I’m either going to get a display case or have it framed someday. His performance of Crystal Man was created specifically for him. 

@guiguou said it to me best yesterday, “You know, Robert Lepage who was the director of Totem chose Joe to be the Crystal Man. In the show he was the first spark of life coming from the sky and created life on earth. He was representing really Life. There was a moment where one of the monkey (there was a lot of monkey characters in the show along with Neanderthals, the show was about evolution of mankind) was removing its monkey skin and revealed that the Crystal man was indeed inside. This moment of the show was expressing that we all had “the Crystal man inside”. This part of divine life is inside everything that lives. That was what Joe represented in the show. After he left the AD in the show started to modify the place of the character in the show so really nobody else did the Crystal man the way Joe did. He was it.”

I miss my Joey so very much. He was and still is my spark of life. What I would give for just one more hug and to hear “I love you so much babe.” just one more time.

Lastly, I’m struggling to make ends meet this month. I had to pay off the funeral home and some other large bills associated with his death. If possible, there’s a GoFundMe set up to help me with these expenses.

https://gofund.me/c914f908

“Sleep strong, my love. I’ll be home soon, and I love you so very much.”

#rip #joeputignano #acrobaddict

A little throwback to our first #Halloween together in 2013 in San Diego. This was Joe’s favorite holiday and we not only went to Disneyland, but also went to Horror Nights at Universal Studios where we got caught in a rainstorm and were soaking wet, and Knott’s Scary Farm that year and had such an awesome time. We’d always go do something this time of year, primarily go ghost hunting at some haunted place or a colonial graveyard. I mis how excited he’d be going to do these places and uncontrollably he’d laugh when I’d jump at something. It’s nice to reminisce over all the adventures we shared but also it hurts. There’s no better way to put it. 

Cherish these memories you make with your husbands, wives, partners, boyfriends, girlfriends, friends and family members. Take pictures and videos and have fun, because it does bring a level of happiness to look back and smile at the things we did. Even though it’s through tears, I can close my eyes and be right back to these fun things we did at the start of our life together.

Finally, I want to that everyone for their amazing generosity through the memorial GoFundMe @leah_meinhart set up to help Pasta, Shadow, and I through this time where I’m lost as to what my next steps in life are going to be as I try to figure everything out. I’m beyond thankful and grateful for those that have helped us out as I’m trying to navigate so very much. Words do not, in any way, shape or form, properly express my gratitude for the donations and the messages I’m receiving. It all is starting to spark a level of hope that I’ll learn to live with this grief and loss, and start to take steps forward while also carrying on Joe’s work and help others the way he did.

https://gofund.me/c914f908

#joeputignano #acrobaddict #rip

I still can’t believe that it’s just been 90-days since you were called to the other side Joe. I still hold onto hope that you’re going to come walking in through the door like nothing  happened. We had several external forces that challenged us at the end of last year and now I’m having to face this fear on my own. 

So as the calendar switches over into a new year where many have high expectations of what may lay ahead and goals they aspire to complete, I’m still trying out how to live this life without you. Pasta and Shadow miss you terribly and I hope you keep visiting us when you can. 

I love you so much babe. Sleep strong, my love.
